                      text: "The V540 is a robust inline-six engine with strong mechanical design. No widespread reliability issues have been reported in well-maintained examples, though carburettor systems may require tuning if used infrequently. Regular oil changes with high-zinc oil, use of 98 RON fuel in high-compression variants, and adherence to 6,000 km service intervals ensure longevity. Restored units show excellent durability with proper running-in.",
