                      text: "Yes. As a modern in-house V8 (2023–present), the V645 has demonstrated strong reliability in Aston Martin’s internal quality reports, with failure rates below 0.6% over two years. The dual-chain timing and robust turbo design are durable when maintained with correct oil (AMOB-004 0W-20) and service intervals. The 2024 turbo update improved transient response and durability. Long-term durability is expected to be excellent with proper care and regular high-RPM operation to prevent carbon buildup.",
