                      text: "Yes. As a modern in-house inline-six (2024–present), the AE24 has demonstrated strong reliability in Aston Martin’s internal quality reports, with failure rates below 0.5% over its first year. The dual-chain timing and robust turbo design are durable when maintained with correct oil (AMOB-006 0W-20) and service intervals. The 2025 turbo update improved transient response and durability. Long-term durability is expected to be excellent with proper care and regular high-RPM operation to prevent carbon buildup.",
