                      text: "The most documented concerns are turbocharger coking from inadequate cooldown, GPF regeneration failures due to short journeys, and 48V hybrid system faults. Oil leaks from timing cover seals have also been noted. These are addressed in Aston Martin service information bulletins with specific diagnostic and repair protocols, including the 2025 turbo blade update (AM-SIB-12-2025) to improve boost control and reduce lag.",
